msgid "The keywords can be selected from the drop-down list or entered directly in the text field."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../effects_and_filters/video_effects/generate/dynamic_text.rst:158
msgid "Timecode keywords are based on the frame rate (fps) and position of the frame. Time-based keywords can include a ``strftime``\\ [#]_ format string to customize the output as long as you put some delimiter except '#' between the keyword and the format string and the keyword comes first. For example, ``#localtime %I:%M:%S %p#`` shows only the time in 12-hour format. The '#' may be escaped with '\\''."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../effects_and_filters/video_effects/generate/dynamic_text.rst:161
msgid "This effect uses the clip's properties for the calculation of the keywords' values. For example, **#timecode#** will start counting at the beginning of the clip and not at the position of the clip in the timeline. **#timecode#** will reset at the start of every clip it is assigned to. In order to have **#timecode#** count across the whole length of your project you must assign the effect to the (main) video track or the Master."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../effects_and_filters/video_effects/generate/dynamic_text.rst:164
msgid ":ref:`Render` option in the render dialog to add time code or frame count to the entire rendered project."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../effects_and_filters/video_effects/generate/dynamic_text.rst:167
msgid "In order to use a semi-transparent background color, click on the color panel, click on :guilabel:`+` and use the horizontal slider to change the transparency."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../effects_and_filters/video_effects/generate/dynamic_text.rst:170
msgid "You can add effects to entire video tracks by clicking on the |tools-wizard| icon in the track header and choosing :menuselection:`Menu --> Sequence --> Add Effect`. Video tracks that have effects added to them have the white |tools-wizard|, tracks without have a grey |tools-wizard| icon. See also :ref:`effects-track_effect`."
msgstr ""

